      <item>
        <title>How to wrap root Frontity in Auth0? and not theme&#39;s index.js</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>No worries, I guessed that that was the case.</p>
<p>I think you’re going to have to figure out why the <code>try</code> is failing. The Frontity site appears to continue to work normally even with the <code>&lt;Auth0Provider&gt;</code> component so I don’t think it’s a Frontity problem. You will need to test what responses you’re getting back from the server in the <code>fetch</code> requests in the <code>try</code> statement, and you may need to read the <code>@auth0/auth0-react</code> documentation to understand what <code>getAccessTokenSilently</code> is doing.</p>
<p>There’s a number of things going on in the <code>try</code> statement so I guess you’ll need to figure out which part is causing the whole <code>try</code> to fail and the <code>catch</code> to execute.</p>
<p>Sorry I’m not able to help you further.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/how-to-wrap-root-frontity-in-auth0-and-not-themes-index-js/2556/15">Read full topic</a></p>
